import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='rate', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of unemployment rate over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(x='state', y='rate', data=data)
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of unemployment rate across different states?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("State")
    plt.ylabel("Unemployment Rate")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')

    plt.ylabel('Average Unemployment Rate')

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='date', y='rate', hue='state', data=data, palette='tab20', legend='brief')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the correlation between unemployment rate and time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Time')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.legend(title='State', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='year', y='rate', bins=50, cbar=True, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of unemployment rate for each year?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
